{{ template "kubee-header" .}}


This {{ template "kubee-app-chart-label" "Kubee App Chart"}} installs
the [Hetzner Csi-driver Helm Chart](https://github.com/hetznercloud/csi-driver/tree/main/chart)
so that you can create external volumes.

{{ template "kubee-installation-instruction" . }}

The `hcloud_token` is mandatory.

{{ template "chart.valuesSection" . }}

## Node Configurations and Limitations

The CSI
plugin [doesn't work on Root Server](https://github.com/hetznercloud/csi-driver/blob/main/docs/kubernetes/integration-with-root-servers.md)
(ie the server should be provided by cloud, not by robot)

You may need to tag them so that no volume is added to them.

```bash
kubectl label nodes <node name> instance.hetzner.cloud/provided-by=robot
```

## Command

### Migration: import an existing volume into CSI

See [how-to-import-volumes](https://github.com/hetznercloud/csi-driver/blob/main/docs/kubernetes/how-to-import-volumes.md)

